.TH greynetic "" "" "X Applications"
.PC "Draw random stippled/color rectangles"
.fi
\fBgreynetic
[\-background \fIcolor\fB]
[\-delay \fIusecs\fB]
[\-display \fIhost:display.screen\fB]
[\-foreground \fIcolor\fB]
[\-mono]
[\-root]
[\-window]\fR
.PP
.B greynetic
draws rectangles of a random size and color, at random positions within
the window.
.PP
.B greynetic
recognizes the following command-line options:
.IP "\fB\-delay \fImicroseconds\fR"
Delay
.I microseconds
between drawing rectangles.
.IP \fB\-mono\fR
Map the application to black and white, even if run on a color server.
.IP \fB\-root\fR
Draw the application in the root window.
.IP \fB\-window\fR
Draw the application in a newly-created window.
This is the default.
.SH "Environmental Variables"
.B greynetic
reads the following environmental variables:
.IP \fBDISPLAY\fR
The default host and display number.
.IP \fBXENVIRONMENT\fR
The name of a resource file that overrides the global resources
stored in the property
.BR RESOURCE_MANAGER .
.SH "See Also"
.B
X,
xscreensaver
.R
